          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Two kinds of target  were  used:  a  sample  of  N-15",
                " enriched  ammonium  sulphate  and high pressure N-15",
                " gas target. the first sample was in form of 108 g of",
                " ((NH-4)2)SO-4))  powder,  enriched to 98 %  in N-15,",
                " and contained in a lucite cylinder with an  internal",
                " diameter  of 37.9 and a length 101.6 mm.  The second",
                " was the  37  g  sample  in  form  of  nitrogen  gas,",
                " enriched  to  98.9  %  in  N-15  contained  in steel",
                " cylinder 2170 mm long and  42.4  mm  outer  diameter",
                " with walls 2.77 mm thick."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PLA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The  resulting  yield  curve  for  each  target",
                " experiment  was  analysed  using  the  variable  bin",
                " Penfold-Leiss method (VBPL).  For ammonium  sulphate",
                " target  because  of  presence  of  nuclei other than",
                " N-15,  in order to deduce the  yield  curve  of  the",
                " desired  reaction  the  additional yield curves both",
                " for sulphur and oxygen samples  have  been  measured",
                " for  target  consisted  of a suspension of 25.6 g of",
                " sulphur in 58.3 g of water contained in an identical",
                " lucite  holder,  and substracted.  Allowance for the",
                " double counting of the N-15(g,2n) reaction was  made",
                " by  substracting  the contribution of the N-15(g,2n)",
                " reaction,  which was  measured  earlier.  The  total",
                " photoabsorption cross section was obtained using the",
                " (g,p) reaction data of Denisov."
              ]
            }
          ],
